  "entities": [
    {
      "id": "14df9187-4b4f-455d-bf3e-17645b61b026",
      "title": "A Cross Knight",
      "url": "http://www.worldanvil.com/world/secret/14df9187-4b4f-455d-bf3e-17645b61b026/edit",
      "content": "“New money. @[[b]Sir Miles Cross[/b]](person:70e226e5-5390-43d3-a466-388964cab7fc) may be the richest man in England, but he’s far from the fine breeding of his betters. He is surly and churlish, prone to arguments that can’t be won and foolish jabs at society. He doesn’t know his place, nor do his children.”"
    },
    {
      "id": "f8683fff-70c2-49c2-b962-1fc129858299",
      "title": "A Foxy Duel for Nash",
      "url": "http://www.worldanvil.com/world/secret/f8683fff-70c2-49c2-b962-1fc129858299/edit",
      "content": "“I’ve heard that @[[b]Lady Nash[/b]](person:e7354503-fa94-48d4-b042-7cc82d1f852a)’s husband, @[Sir Grover Nash](person:487073d6-53ef-4041-be07-a784e9bdf4ba), nearly dueled @[[b]Lt. Foxsmith[/b]](person:71777950-6f6e-41ce-896c-ce17f10a5752) once… I wonder for what. Of course he's dead now, but nobody ever would have called the old chap a duellist…”"
    },
    {
      "id": "7250bcf8-7ee0-4bde-a5b3-a551454efc82",
      "title": "A Swift Pirate",
      "url": "http://www.worldanvil.com/world/secret/7250bcf8-7ee0-4bde-a5b3-a551454efc82/edit",
      "content": "“He must have been a pirate. He must have been. No seaman has ever become that rich through honest work, I’ll bet on it. @[[b]Captain Swift[/b]](person:76a76a8b-0559-4164-af49-a1208d83a92f) plays the innocent, but just a merchant? Fah! He’s stolen from the crown. Must have.”"
    },
    {
      "id": "c3cff4bc-5d80-4518-8b19-f615f69706c4",
      "title": "A Swift Romance in a Davenport",
      "url": "http://www.worldanvil.com/world/secret/c3cff4bc-5d80-4518-8b19-f615f69706c4/edit",
      "content": "“@[[b]Lady Davenport[/b]](person:f28edc4e-305d-4dd9-b45d-a34dc0baec44) and @[[b]Captain Swift[/b]](person:76a76a8b-0559-4164-af49-a1208d83a92f) used to court, an age ago. That was before she married, of course. She’d promised to wait for him, but he was lost at sea for many months - and when he returned she’d thought him dead and married another. It was all quite the dramatic tragedy.”"
    },
    {
      "id": "ce5df5ab-4640-4e97-bcc1-9859c08a6647",
      "title": "A Swift-Constructed Workhouse",
      "url": "http://www.worldanvil.com/world/secret/ce5df5ab-4640-4e97-bcc1-9859c08a6647/edit",
      "content": "“It’ll be just another workhouse whatever @[[b]Captain Monty Swift[/b]](person:76a76a8b-0559-4164-af49-a1208d83a92f) builds, you mark my words. Nobody really cares about foundling children except what money they can make off of them. I don’t believe ‘Christian generosity’ as his reason for a minute.”"
    },
    {
      "id": "829b1043-16d4-469f-aa3a-aab39b99f951",
      "title": "Alice or Anne for Hastings",
      "url": "http://www.worldanvil.com/world/secret/829b1043-16d4-469f-aa3a-aab39b99f951/edit",
      "content": "“@[[b]Miss Alice Middleton[/b]](person:ea7fe390-1d1b-40a0-8566-ada617dbace8) is quite a sweet girl, but gets overshadowed by all her boisterous sisters. Kind to a fault, if not a bit silly. I’ve heard she and her sister @[[b]Miss Anne[/b]](person:9625c3b5-2e26-4844-9ae1-68bcc035878a) are both hoping @[[b]Mr. Hastings[/b]](person:e5a26d73-7dba-4e36-b5b5-535babc1766d) will court them, but that boy seems rather a mess, doesn’t he?”"
    },
